       <br />
       This is a community who welcomes visitors from all over the country and at the recent surf lifesaving national titles, the commute between the beach and water events (at North Kirra) and the surfboat arena (at Tugun) involved a death-defying cycle/walk along Golden Four Drive.
       <br />
       Why build a walkway from Rainbow Bay to North Kirra, and not beyond?  Is it for the sake of a few homeowners (likely rental accomodation)?
       <br />
       Are we not living in a society currently suffering from obesity and other issues derived from lack of exercise and healthy living?
       <br />
       This pathway encourages lifestyle changes that directly combat this continuous battle for our younger generations.  I personally would not want my grandchildren cycling their bikes along the main highway, sucking the fumes from exhaust pipes.  I am sure the local health professionals would agree with me!
       <br />
       Wake up Gold Coast City Council and do what the people voted you in to do....the right thing by all.
